   <conbody>
      <hazardstatement type="notice" class="+ topic/note hazard-d/hazardstatement ">
         <messagepanel class="+ topic/ul hazard-d/messagepanel ">
            <typeofhazard class="+ topic/li hazard-d/typeofhazard ">loss of output voltage</typeofhazard>
            <howtoavoid class="+ topic/li hazard-d/howtoavoid ">If the system is turned off without the external manual
bypass in <b class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b ">Bypass</b> the output voltage is lost.</howtoavoid>
            <howtoavoid class="+ topic/li hazard-d/howtoavoid ">When the external manual bypass switch is in <b class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b ">Bypass</b> position, it is not possible for the system to automatically switch
back to inverter operation in case the bypass mains becomes unavailable.</howtoavoid>
            <howtoavoid class="+ topic/li hazard-d/howtoavoid ">Always coordinate maintenance and turning off or on the
system with the users of the consumers. Make sure that users of the
connected consumers are informed before proceeding.</howtoavoid>
         </messagepanel>
      </hazardstatement>
      <p class="- topic/p ">This function check describes how to perform a basic function check
on a single system or one unit in a system with multiple units.</p>
      <ol class="- topic/ol ">
         <li class="- topic/li ">
            <p class="- topic/p ">Check that the system is in normal operation and that no alarms
are active.</p>
         </li>
         <li platform="WxW" class="- topic/li ">
            <p class="- topic/p ">Open the inverter input switch.</p>
         </li>
         <li platform="PxW WxW" class="- topic/li ">
            <p class="- topic/p ">Check that the system switches to bypass
operation and that the <b class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b ">Display</b> shows <codeph class="+ topic/ph pr-d/codeph ">Bypass operation</codeph>.</p>
         </li>
         <li platform="WxW" class="- topic/li ">
            <p class="- topic/p ">Charge the DC capacitors:</p>
            <ol class="- topic/ol ">
               <li class="- topic/li ">
                  <p class="- topic/p ">Keep the charging/discharging switch it in position 2 (charge)
until the warning LED turns off.</p>
               </li>
               <li class="- topic/li ">
                  <p class="- topic/p ">With the charging/discharging switch still in position 2 (charge),
close the inverter input switch. If not possible, release the charging/discharging
switch and quickly close the inverter input switch.</p>
               </li>
               <li class="- topic/li ">
                  <p class="- topic/p ">Release the charging/discharging switch.</p>
               </li>
            </ol>
         </li>
         <li class="- topic/li ">
            <p class="- topic/p ">Check that the system switches to normal operation and that
the <b class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b ">Display</b> shows <codeph platform="PxW WxW" class="+ topic/ph pr-d/codeph ">Normal operation
load power ...%</codeph>.</p>
         </li>
         <li platform="PxW WxW" class="- topic/li ">
            <p class="- topic/p ">Switch to bypass operation:</p>
            <ol conref="1220236_How_to_Switch_from_Normal_Operation_to_Bypass_Operation_CPT_DD00545782.dita#HowToSwitchFromNormalOperationToByp-5AF57FF1/Switch-to-bypass_1220236"
                class="- topic/ol ">
               <li class="- topic/li "/>
            </ol>
         </li>
         <li platform="PxW WxW" class="- topic/li ">
            <p class="- topic/p ">Check that the <b class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b ">Display</b> shows <codeph class="+ topic/ph pr-d/codeph ">Bypass operation</codeph>.</p>
         </li>
         <li otherprops="2pMBS" class="- topic/li ">
            <p class="- topic/p ">Turn the external manual bypass switch to
the <b class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b ">Bypass</b> position.</p>
         </li>
         <li class="- topic/li ">
            <p class="- topic/p ">Check that the red <b class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b ">Manual bypass on</b> LED is active on
the alarm panel and that the green manual bypass LED is active on
the mimic diagram.</p>
         </li>
         <li class="- topic/li ">
            <p class="- topic/p ">Turn off the system, press both the <b class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b ">ON button</b> and the <b class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b ">OFF button</b> for two seconds. The <b class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b ">Display</b> shows <codeph class="+ topic/ph pr-d/codeph ">Standby</codeph>.</p>
         </li>
         <li class="- topic/li ">
            <p class="- topic/p ">Measure the output voltage.</p>
         </li>
         <li class="- topic/li ">
            <p class="- topic/p ">Turn on the system, press the <b class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b ">ON button</b> for one second.
After a few seconds the <b class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b ">Display</b> shows <codeph class="+ topic/ph pr-d/codeph ">Normal operation
load power ...%</codeph>.</p>
         </li>
         <li class="- topic/li ">
            <p class="- topic/p ">Switch to bypass operation:</p>
            <ol conref="1220236_How_to_Switch_from_Normal_Operation_to_Bypass_Operation_CPT_DD00545782.dita#HowToSwitchFromNormalOperationToByp-5AF57FF1/Switch-to-bypass_1220236"
                class="- topic/ol ">
               <li class="- topic/li "/>
            </ol>
         </li>
         <li class="- topic/li ">
            <p class="- topic/p ">The <b class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b ">Display</b> shows <codeph class="+ topic/ph pr-d/codeph ">Bypass operation</codeph>.</p>
         </li>
         <li class="- topic/li ">
            <p class="- topic/p ">Turn the manual bypass switch to the <b class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b ">UPS</b> position.</p>
         </li>
         <li platform="PxW WxW" class="- topic/li ">
            <p class="- topic/p ">Switch to normal operation:</p>
            <ol conref="1220236_How_to_Switch_from_Bypass_Operation_to_Normal_Operation_CPT_DD00545781.dita#HowToSwitchFromBypassOperationToNor-5AF6A01C/Switch-to-normal_1220236"
                class="- topic/ol ">
               <li class="- topic/li "/>
            </ol>
         </li>
         <li platform="PxW WxW" class="- topic/li ">
            <p class="- topic/p ">The <b class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b ">Display</b> shows <codeph class="+ topic/ph pr-d/codeph ">Normal
operation load power ...%</codeph>.</p>
         </li>
         <li class="- topic/li ">
            <p class="- topic/p ">Reset any alarms by pressing the <b class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b ">C key</b> twice.</p>
         </li>
         <li class="- topic/li ">
            <p class="- topic/p ">Make sure the system operates correctly and no alarms are present.</p>
         </li>
      </ol>
